# Ctrl+Alt+Deplete: An Interactive E-Waste Sculpture

Ctrl+Alt+Deplete is a sculptural installation that brings to life the image of a solitary tree mutated with electronic waste, emerging from a landfill. Constructed entirely from discarded electronics—keyboards, wires, broken monitors, motherboards, and phone fragments—alongside other post-consumer trash, the tree stands as a haunting monument to our age of overconsumption and obsolescence.

## Installation Components

### 1. Physical Sculpture
- Constructed from e-waste and consumer trash
- Tree-like structure emerging from simulated landfill
- Materials include:
  - Discarded keyboards
  - Electronic wires
  - Broken monitors
  - Motherboards
  - Phone fragments
  - Other post-consumer waste

### 2. Interactive Control System
- Built using Processing
- Translates viewer interaction into MIDI signals
- Controls include:
  - Mouse movement tracking
  - Position-based parameter modulation
  - Real-time response to viewer presence

### 3. Sound Generation
- Implemented in Strudel (TidalCycles)
- Complex, layered soundscape featuring:
  - Environmental speech synthesis
  - Multiple sound patterns
  - Real-time modulation
  - Visual feedback through Hydra

## Technical Architecture

### Processing Component
- Handles interactive elements
- Converts physical interaction to MIDI
- Uses loopMIDI for virtual MIDI communication
- Controls multiple parameters:
  - Master volume
  - Delay effects
  - Room/reverb
  - Pattern speed
  - Panning

### Sound Design
- Layered composition with:
  - Speech synthesis of environmental terms
  - Sine wave patterns
  - Environmental sound effects
  - Number sequences
  - Real-time modulation
  - Visual feedback

### Integration
- Uses loopMIDI as virtual MIDI bridge
- Processing sends MIDI control messages (CC values 1-5)
- Strudel receives and processes MIDI data
- Creates responsive sound environment

